SIMPLE: occurrent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Occurrent
<hw>Oc*cur"rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>occurrens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>occurrere</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>occurrent</ets>. See <er>Occur</er>.]</ety> <def>Occurring
or happening; hence, incidental; accidental.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Occurrent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Occurrent
<hw>Oc*cur"rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who meets; hence, an adversary.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything that happens; an occurrence.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These we must meet with in obvious <qex>occurrents</qex> of the
world.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Occurse</ent>⟦br⟧
